Provides a control loop, adding a data item to the queue at the
configured frequency.

@overrides the Thread run method

Add Experiment:

Add a new experiment to the dict of experiments. It follows the format:
     { name: { fields : {name: '', required: bool}, summary: '' } }

Line Items.

A QWidget that accepts a list of labels + button pairs. These items must have the following structure:
    {
        'item label': {
            'button1 label': {
                'color': 'color of the button',
                'textColor': 'color of the button text',
                'action': action of button (a python method)
            },
            'button2 label': {
                'color': 'color of the button',
                'textColor': 'color of the button text',
                'action': action of button (a python method)
            },
        }
    }

Add field:

Add a new field to the dict of fields. It follows the format:
     { name: { help_text: '', type: int} }

Load Experiment Fields.

{
    'fields': [{}, {}],
    'summary': ''
}

Using the experiment dictionary, loop over the field keys and put them in a list.
